# Always Update Documentation

## CRITICAL: Documentation Must Stay Current
When making any code changes, you MUST update the corresponding documentation:

## API Changes
- **New endpoints** → Update [OpenAPI docs](mdc:src/main/resources/openapi/documentation.yaml)
- **New endpoints** → Update [Postman collection](mdc:postman_collection.json)
- **Authentication changes** → Update both OpenAPI and Postman
- **Validation changes** → Update examples and error responses

## Project Changes
- **New file types** → Update Cursor rules with new glob patterns
- **New workflows** → Update Cursor commands with new procedures
- **Structure changes** → Update file references in rules
- **Technology updates** → Update all relevant documentation

## Documentation Files
- [src/main/resources/openapi/documentation.yaml](mdc:src/main/resources/openapi/documentation.yaml) - API documentation
- [postman_collection.json](mdc:postman_collection.json) - API testing collection
- [.cursor/rules/](mdc:.cursor/rules) - Cursor rules directory
- [.cursor/commands/](mdc:.cursor/commands/) - Cursor commands
- [.cursor/instructions/](mdc:.cursor/instructions/) - Cursor instructions directory
- [README.md](mdc:README.md) - Project overview

## Update Commands
Use these commands to keep documentation current:
- **`update-documentation`** - Comprehensive documentation update
- **`update-swagger-postman`** - Quick API documentation update
- **`maintain-cursor-config`** - Cursor rules and commands maintenance

## Validation
Always validate documentation after updates:
```bash
# Validate OpenAPI
python -c "import yaml; yaml.safe_load(open('src/main/resources/openapi/documentation.yaml'))"

# Validate Postman
python -c "import json; json.load(open('postman_collection.json'))"

# Test Swagger UI
curl -s http://localhost:8080/swagger | head -20
```